  <div class="auction-body">
    <div class="auction-description">
      <h2>Skills</h2>
      Backbone.js, Chai, JavaScript, Mocha, Node.js, and Sails.js
      <p><strong>Scenario: Authenticated user sees on a participant&#39;s profile page all the opportunities they&#39;ve been assigned or completed</strong></p>

<ul>
<li>Given I am an authenticated user</li>
<li>And there is a participant</li>
<li>And that participant has participated in an opportunity</li>
<li>When I go to that participant&#39;s profile page</li>
<li>Then I should see the name of each opportunity listed in the section labeled &quot;Participated&quot;</li>
<li>And I should see the created date of that opportunity</li>
<li>And I should see the status of that opportunity (Assigned or Completed)</li>
<li>And the opportunity name should link to the show page for that opportunity (<a href="https://openopps.18f.gov/tasks/%5Bid%5D">https://openopps.18f.gov/tasks/[id]</a>)</li>
</ul>

<h2>General acceptance criteria</h2>

<ul>
<li>Test coverage stays the same or increases</li>
<li>Tests pass</li>
<li><strong>A payment URL is specified in your micro-purchase profile so we can pay the award</strong></li>
</ul>

<h2>Notes</h2>

<p>When a person participates in and completes an Opportunity it is not showing in their profile. The example is Jessica Skretch who just completed Be a Mobile Tester for DHS.gov
(<a href="https://openopps.digitalgov.gov/tasks/547">https://openopps.digitalgov.gov/tasks/547</a>).</p>

<p><img src="https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/9039852/19327594/b506a33a-909d-11e6-824f-ee6478f496c6.png" alt="screen shot 2016-10-12 at 5 01 22 pm"></p>

<p><img width="1166" alt="screen shot 2016-10-14 at 12 36 38 pm" src="https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/100149/19400402/e58023ce-920a-11e6-9e0f-41abbc20d83f.png"></p>

<p>Use the label design below for the &quot;Assigned/Completed&quot; indicators</p>

<p><img src="https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/100149/19524066/6070103e-95d1-11e6-9e50-7259c77b5699.png" alt="screen shot 2016-10-19 at 10 51 05 am"></p>

    </div>
